    pearls: ["Ultrasound guidance is the standard of care for peripheral nerve blocks - improves success rates, reduces complications, and allows real-time visualization of local anesthetic spread", "Calculate maximum local anesthetic doses BEFORE the procedure: lidocaine 4.5 mg/kg (7 with epi), bupivacaine 2.5 mg/kg, ropivacaine 3 mg/kg. Exceeding these doses risks LAST", "20% intralipid emulsion must be immediately accessible wherever regional anesthesia is performed - it is the definitive treatment for bupivacaine-induced cardiac arrest", "ASRA guidelines for anticoagulation timing are essential: LMWH hold 12 hours (prophylactic) or 24 hours (therapeutic) before neuraxial procedures; resume 4-6 hours post-procedure", "Fascia iliaca compartment block for hip fracture pain is one of the most impactful NP-performed nerve blocks - reduces opioid requirements by 50-70% and decreases delirium risk in elderly patients"],
